		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=klovensky&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Greetings Istartion, <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  welcome to the word of the paladin.:)With you <br>being a Ranger i need not tell you of the difficulty and the joy of playing a hybrid. Paladins is a great class as my main is one and i have enjoyed playing as him for over a year now. Used right, paladins can be a strong link in the success of a guild, used wrongly and we are uterly worthless. <br><br>    Starting as a human is a great idea (i assume you are human hense your start in Freeport) since humans get a great balance of stats. I hope you placed your starting 20 points into STA. This will become your most important stat in the upper end of the game (next to AC that is). If not it is fine, there are many good STA items out there for paladins. A good rule for AC is to keep it at 25 * your level. <br><br>     Paladins do not acquire Dual Wield, which is fine since we are not DPSers anyhow. I suggest practicing your 2hs over anything. Most of the upper weapons we recieve are this (i am excluding our epics)<br><br>    What i find Paladins are the best at is Aggro control, and every paladin will (or should) back me up on this. This is why, in my opinion, a good paladin is by far the best tank in the game. At the higher end, when your wizards, mages, rangers :) and other DPSers are making the mobs their prison buddies, it makes it hard for the tanks to keep aggro. A 800 hp fire nuke would piss me off more than a 120 slash across the knee, would it you? Warriors have a hard time holding aggro, but paladins (and shadow knights) are masters at keeping little mr. Sentry of Justice or whom ever else your fighting, at bay. <br><br>     What gives us this oh so great Advantage is our line of stun spells. I keep my 4 best memed at all times. Chain stunning not only keeps aggro on you, but it helps in your own damage as well as some take away HP as well as stun. Plus, you get in better hits when the mob is sitting their looking at you like a retard :)<br><br>    This brings me to my next point. Now you can either grab yourself a KEI from PoK, which works fine. But i suggest having a good amount of WIS, at least 150 (in the higher end that is) to help you keep mana for the stunning, and healing if the moment calls for it. This is another reason why i love my paladin, if you cleric is in trouble or happens to run OOM in a tough fight. You can help out with your own line of healing spells. Now dont expect to heal like the cleric does, you wont. But we do have efficient enough healing to save a life you two. <br><br>       This is the advice i bring to you for now, if you have any other questions please feel free to ask. <br><br>Baldev Utumno<br>53 Paladin of Karana<br><br>&quot;Knowledge is Power, Ignorance is Bliss...........you decide.&quot;<br>       <br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
