		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Aug 28th 3:18 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10619533459389&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=106209757951897"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=106209757951897></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=250051"><span id=Scholar>Anglish</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>51 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anglish&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Paladins are a bit different from rangers. First, the lack of a dual wield skill is most noticable. Second, the ability to wear plate instead of chain armor is easy to see. Third, the ability to Bash is an obvious difference in the paladin.<br><br>If you focus on these three differences, you will see that:<br>1. Paladins have lower offensive potential than Rangers in melee<br>2. Paladins have better defensive potential than Rangers in melee<br>3. Paladins have a very strong ability against casters<br><br>Here's the list of skill caps from Caster's Realm (which may or may not be completely accurate):<br><br><u>Skill Caps</u><br><br><i>Paladin:</i><br>Most Weapons - 225<br>Offense - 225<br>Defense - 252<br><br><i>Ranger:</i><br>Most Weapons - 250<br>Offense - 252<br>Defense - 200<br><br>If you examine the difference in skill caps, you'll see that the paladin has a defensive focus while the ranger is more offensive. While you'll definitely find yourself missing the ability to snare and fear animals, you have a strong line of spells for fighting undead. Unrest will undoubtedly become your playground in the upper 20s and low 30s, since you can be a &quot;stealth knight&quot; (ducking around with Invisibility Vs. Undead) as well as make use of the Instrument of Nife spell/proc (after level 30).<br><br>As a paladin, I found that crowd control was a fun ability. When you get the root spell, you can save a lot of butts with the &quot;root and scoot&quot; technique. Also, when the situation calls for a &quot;pealer&quot;, I found that the Blindness spell was an incredible taunt for pealing a MOB off a caster quickly (but will cause a MOB to run wildly if contact is broken). Also the stun line of spells works as a major taunt too, rendering the MOB motionless to allow the healer time to heal a caster and let the caster move off. With healing, stuns, rooting and Lay of Hands, paladins are experts at &quot;saving the day&quot;.<br><br>Despite what some people may argue, paladins can solo even at high levels. They use their defensive skills to outlast an opponent in melee, then use Root and their good healing spells to go another round of melee, Root and Heal again until finally the foe is finished.<br><br>I can think of so many more things I like about the paladin, but I'll keep it short and just say that you've picked a really fun class.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Aug 28 15:44:14 2003</em></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><b><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=759986 target=akztarg>Anglish Wildwood</a></b><br><i>Ranger of Luclin</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10619533459389&num=4&page=&post=1&mid=10619533459389><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">4 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
